==Dogs in the Park==
===Talking to Cecilia===
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|Talk about the Christmas event.}}
** '''Cecilia:''' Greetings! If you have come to gaze in rapture at the natural beauty of Falador's parkland, then I have bad news.
** '''Player:''' Oh no! What happened?
** '''Cecilia:''' We got some impromptu visitors to the park. They came out of nowhere and made an awful mess of the place.
** '''Cecilia:''' They trampled the flowers, startled the ducks, dug new holes in the ground...
** '''Player:''' That's terrible. Who are these hooligans?
** '''Cecilia:''' That's not all! I had plans to decorate the park for Christmas, and they went and chewed some of the decorations.
** '''Player:''' How deplorable! Wait, did you say 'chew'? What kind of visitors are you talking about?
** '''Cecilia:''' Why, they're dogs of course! I'm quite upset, yet they are so cute that I can't stay mad. We can't leave them here, however.
** '''Cecilia:''' I'm going to need some help to find them a place to be, and to clean up afterwards.
** {{tcond|If the player didn't complete the 2024 Halloween event:}}
*** '''Player:''' And you're about to ask me.
*** '''Cecilia:''' Quite right! So... Will you help?
*** {{tact|continue}}
** {{tcond|If the player completed the 2024 Halloween event:}}
*** '''Player:''' Relocate some intruders and clean up the mess they made? I did something just like that a month or two ago.
*** '''Cecilia:''' It sounds like you are perfect for the job, then! Will you help?
*** {{tact|continue}}
** {{tselect|Start the Christmas event?}}
** {{topt|Yes.}}
*** '''Player:''' I will!
*** '''Cecilia:''' Oh, thank you!
*** '''Cecilia:''' I've reached out to one of my acquaintances, Probita, and she confirmed to me that none of these five adorable little tykes have an owner.
*** '''Cecilia:''' As cute as they are, they cannot just stay here.
*** '''Player:''' Maybe I could take them off your hands?
*** '''Cecilia:''' You can try, but I cannot promise that they wouldn't attempt to ransack all of your belongings. You saw what happened to the park.
*** '''Player:''' Good point. I do prefer when my belongings stay in one piece.
*** '''Cecilia:''' I wonder if they caused so much havoc because they came in as a group.
*** {{tcond|If the player is a [[group ironman]]:}}
**** '''Player:''' In fairness, it can be fun being in a group. I can see where they're coming from.
**** {{tact|continue}}
*** '''Cecilia:''' We should be able to manage this by getting each of them a different loving owner and some proper training.
*** '''Cecilia:''' I've already got a few ideas for potential adopters. Hmm... What if we set up a rehoming event? An adoption drive!
*** '''Player:''' That could work!
*** '''Cecilia:''' We could have balloons and decorations, and maybe even nibbles.
*** '''Player:''' Wouldn't the dogs eat the nibbles and chew the decorations?
*** '''Cecilia:''' You're right, of course. Then... What if we dressed up the dogs to make them extra cute. Would that distract them enough?
*** '''Player:''' I don't know. It might distract them from the decorations, but I don't think anything could distract them from the nibbles.
*** '''Cecilia:''' Yes, that is true. Let us not have the nibbles. Besides, the first step is to secure some costumes and a venue.
*** '''Cecilia:''' While I try and figure out where the best place to host the event is, could you please check with Party Pete if he would have costumes to lend us? I will also start writing and decorating the invitations in the meantime.
*** '''Player:''' On it!
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|No.}}
*** '''Player:''' I'd love to help, but I'm somewhat busy right now.
*** '''Cecilia:''' Then I will have to wrangle those dogs myself. We can't leave the park in that state!
*** {{tact|end}}
